name: Luftwaffe Airbus A400M [54+06] Taxi and Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
YYC has briefly turned into an Air Force Base! Yesterday, July 6th, we received three surprise military visitors from Germany, Spain, and France, bringing troops and equipment for NATO training at CFB Suffield, a Canadian Forces Base southeast of Calgary. This occurs every year, with it comes some interesting military visitors! I'm usually not able to see them all, but fortunately, I was able to see at least one special visitor in the air, in the form of this Luftwaffe A400M departing (presumably) back to Germany. ATC is included, hope you enjoy my first video of an A400M departing.

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
